Hughes Fabrice Zango of Burkina Faso became the first man to triple jump beyond 18 metres indoors on Saturday at a meet in Aubiere, France. He improved the world record under a roof to 18.07m. Zango, a world championship bronze medallist from 2019 and African champion, added 15cm to the previous record of 17.92m from Frenchman Teddy Tamgho, who is his coach. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He made the record jump in the sixth and final attempt. The outdoor world record stands at 18.29m from Briton Jonathan Edwards in 1995.